parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes a knocking or clunking noise
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine warning light illuminates
smoke or flames come from the engine compartment
coolant leaks
the vehicle overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs can lead to continued driving of vehicles with potentially faulty engines, increasing the risk of accidents or engine failure.
symptoms: The part to do the recall repair is unavailable
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignoring engine warning lights can lead to engine failure, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
the service engine soon warning light illuminates
the charging system warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column coupler can cause the steering wheel to shake, rattle, or vibrate, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The steering wheel rattles
clunks
or shakes when driving
turning
or going over bumps; the steering wheel makes a clicking or knocking sound; the steering column has play or looseness; the vehicle's airbag light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes tight or difficult to turn; the vehicle's power steering warning light illuminates; the vehicle's EPS (Electric Power Steering) system fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal drops to the floor
the brake warning light illuminates
the vehicle experiences sudden and unexpected braking
the parking brake engages unexpectedly
the vehicle makes grinding noises
the vehicle swerves or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake warning light illuminates
the vehicle experiences sudden and unexpected braking
the parking brake engages unexpectedly
the vehicle makes grinding noises
the vehicle swerves or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving recall repair parts can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle owner receives notification of a recall but is unable to obtain the necessary repair parts
the vehicle owner experiences frustration and concern about the safety of their vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Check Charging System" warning light comes on
the vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the battery level drops
the engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the brakes malfunction
the dashboard lights flicker or go blank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The "Check Brake" warning light comes on
the brakes drop to the floor
the vehicle barely stops
the brakes make a grudging noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the acceleration system can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the vehicle suddenly gains speed without touching the gas pedal
the acceleration is slow or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Smoke comes out of the dash
wires smell like they're burning
the dashboard lights flicker or go blank
the vehicle's systems shut down completely.
